Feral/Verdant:




Feral looked back to Verdant and sighed.  "Hurry up and stop chasing the 
wildlife.  We got what we came for." he said, nodding his head towards the 
furry mammal he was dragging by a leg.

Verdant snarled a few times in his newfound language, following Feral more 
quickly now.

"Don't speak to me like that.  Would you rather I not help you and let you go 
wandering around the jungle for the rest of your days?"

With a few grunts from Verdant, Feral smiled triumphantly.  "I thought not."
